   $f(0) + f(2x) = 2f(x)g(-x)$.

Comparing the equations from $y = x$ and $y = -x$: $f(2x) + f(0) = 2f(x)g(x)$ and $f(0) + f(2x) = 2f(x)g(-x)$, we get $2f(x)g(x) = 2f(x)g(-x)$. If $f(x) \neq 0$, then $g(x) = g(-x)$.

