   $f(0) + f(t) = 2f\left(\frac{t}{2}\right)g\left(-\frac{t}{2}\right)$.

Since $g$ is even (from previous step), $g(-\frac{t}{2}) = g(\frac{t}{2})$, so $f(0) + f(t) = 2f\left(\frac{t}{2}\right)g\left(\frac{t}{2}\right)$, which is the same as the equation from $x = \frac{t}{2}$, $y = \frac{t}{2}$. This is consistent.

